import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    data = data[['location', 'precipitation']]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="location", y="precipitation", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set(xlabel='Location', ylabel='Precipitation')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle and New York?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']
    data = data[['date', 'temp_max']]
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['temp_max'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[data['location'] == 'New York']
    sns.scatterplot(x='wind', y='temp_max', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and temperature in New York?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed')
    plt.ylabel('Maximum Temperature')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['count'] = 1
    data = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).count().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='location', y='count', hue='weather', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the most common type of weather in Seattle and New York?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Weather', loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by=['date'])
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_min', hue='location', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the minimum temperature vary over time in Seattle and New York?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Minimum Temperature')
    plt.legend(title='Location', loc='upper left', labels=['New York', 'Seattle'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
